The paper discusses the behavior of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for data-driven simulation of noisy dynamical systems. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically, neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also deals with the dynamics of the system, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the ability of the RNN to adjust to changes in input data, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
